Comment in
    Eye (Lond). 2019 Oct;33(10):1664-1674.

Acute primary angle closure requires emergency management that involves a rapid 
lowering of the intraocular pressure and resolution of relative pupil block - 
the most common mechanism of angle closure. Emergency strategies for lowering 
intraocular pressure include medical treatment and argon laser peripheral 
